### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  GTFS INTERPRETER API — 44 endpoints (REST Client collection)
###
###  Usage: install the "humao.rest-client" extension then click
###  "Send Request" above each request.
###
###  Environment variables: settings.json > rest-client.environmentVariables
###  Toggle between "local" (direct API :3004) and "dev-docker" (via nginx /api).
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3004/gtfs
@sessionId = test-session-uuid-1234-5678-9abcdef0

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HEALTH & BASE
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Healthcheck
GET http://localhost:3004/health

### 2. Root welcome
GET http://localhost:3004/

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  UPLOAD & SAMPLE
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3. Upload a GTFS ZIP (replace the path)
# @name uploadGtfs
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="gtfsZip"; filename="sample.zip"
Content-Type: application/zip

< ./GTFS-EXPRESS-API/sample/sample.zip
------boundary--

### 4. Load bundled sample GTFS
GET {{baseUrl}}/load-sample
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 5. Upload stats (admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/upload-stats
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  READ: AGENCIES / ROUTES / DIRECTIONS / STOPS & TIMES
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6. List agencies
GET {{baseUrl}}/agencies
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 7. List routes for an agency
GET {{baseUrl}}/routes/AGENCY-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 8. List directions for a route at a given date
GET {{baseUrl}}/directions/ROUTE-1/20260415
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 9. Stops & times for a route/direction/date
GET {{baseUrl}}/stops_and_times/ROUTE-1/0/20260415
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 10. Shapes for a route/direction
GET {{baseUrl}}/shapes/ROUTE-1/0
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 11. All shapes of the network
GET {{baseUrl}}/all_shapes
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 12. Shapes for a specific route
GET {{baseUrl}}/shapes_for_route/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  READ: CALENDARS
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 13. Calendar for a route
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 14. Calendar_dates for a route
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar_dates/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 15. Calendar by service_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar_service/SERVICE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 16. Calendar_dates by service_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar_dates_service/SERVICE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  READ: STATS
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 17. Average trip times
GET {{baseUrl}}/average_trip_times
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 18. Global statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/statistics
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  READ: DETAILS & SEARCH
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 20. Stop detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/stop_detail/STOP-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 21. Route detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/route_detail/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 22. Trip detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/trip_detail/TRIP-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 23. Global search
GET {{baseUrl}}/search?q=Châtelet&limit=20
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  EDIT SESSION: ENTER / EXIT / STATUS
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 24. Enter edit mode (migrates CSV → SQLite)
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/enter
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 25. Exit edit mode (drops edits unless exported)
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/exit
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 26. Edit mode status
GET {{baseUrl}}/edit/status
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : STOPS
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 27. Update a stop
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/edit/stops/STOP-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "stop_name": "Châtelet — Les Halles",
  "platform_code": "A",
  "wheelchair_boarding": "1"
}

### 28. Create a stop
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/stops
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "stop_id": "STOP-NEW-42",
  "stop_name": "New Stop",
  "stop_lat": 48.8566,
  "stop_lon": 2.3522,
  "location_type": 0
}

### 29. Delete a stop (refused if referenced)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/edit/stops/STOP-NEW-42
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : ROUTES
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 30. Update a route
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/edit/routes/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "route_long_name": "Châtelet ↔ Mairie d'Issy",
  "route_color": "FF5733",
  "route_text_color": "FFFFFF"
}

### 31. Delete a route (cascade: trips → stop_times → frequencies → orphan shapes/calendars)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/edit/routes/ROUTE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : TRIPS
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 32. Update a trip
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/edit/trips/TRIP-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "trip_headsign": "Mairie d'Issy",
  "direction_id": "0",
  "wheelchair_accessible": "1",
  "bikes_allowed": "2"
}

### 33. Create a trip
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/trips
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "trip_id": "TRIP-NEW-01",
  "route_id": "ROUTE-1",
  "service_id": "SERVICE-1",
  "trip_headsign": "Terminus",
  "direction_id": "0"
}

### 34. Duplicate a trip (via create with source_trip_id + time_offset)
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/trips
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "trip_id": "TRIP-DUP-01",
  "source_trip_id": "TRIP-1",
  "time_offset_minutes": 30
}

### 35. Delete a trip (cascade stop_times + frequencies)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/edit/trips/TRIP-NEW-01
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : STOP_TIMES
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 36. Update a stop_time (PK composite trip_id + stop_sequence)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/edit/stop_times/TRIP-1/5
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "arrival_time": "08:15:00",
  "departure_time": "08:15:30",
  "pickup_type": "0",
  "drop_off_type": "0"
}

### 37. Create a stop_time
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/stop_times
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "trip_id": "TRIP-1",
  "stop_sequence": 99,
  "stop_id": "STOP-1",
  "arrival_time": "25:30:00",
  "departure_time": "25:30:30"
}

### 38. Delete a stop_time
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/edit/stop_times/TRIP-1/99
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : CALENDAR & CALENDAR_DATES
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 39. Update a calendar (weekly pattern + date range)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/edit/calendar/SERVICE-1
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "monday": 1,
  "tuesday": 1,
  "wednesday": 1,
  "thursday": 1,
  "friday": 1,
  "saturday": 0,
  "sunday": 0,
  "start_date": "20260101",
  "end_date": "20261231"
}

### 40. Create a calendar_date exception
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/calendar_dates
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "service_id": "SERVICE-1",
  "date": "20261225",
  "exception_type": 2
}

### 41. Delete a calendar_date
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/edit/calendar_dates/SERVICE-1/20261225
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  MUTATIONS : BULK DELETE (atomic, single _edit_log entry per batch)
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 42. Bulk delete stops (atomic — refuses if any stop has stop_times or children)
### Returns: { deletedCount, deletedIds, cascadedCounts }
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/stops/bulk-delete
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "ids": ["STOP-A", "STOP-B", "STOP-C"]
}

### 43. Bulk delete routes (cascade: trips → stop_times → frequencies + orphan shapes/calendars)
### Returns: { deletedCount, deletedIds, cascadedCounts: { trips, stop_times, frequencies, orphan_shapes, orphan_calendars } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/routes/bulk-delete
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "ids": ["ROUTE-1", "ROUTE-2"]
}

### 44. Bulk delete trips (cascade: stop_times + frequencies)
### Returns: { deletedCount, deletedIds, cascadedCounts: { stop_times, frequencies } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/trips/bulk-delete
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "ids": ["TRIP-1", "TRIP-2", "TRIP-3"]
}

### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HISTORY, UNDO & EXPORT
### ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 45. Edit history (reads _edit_log)
GET {{baseUrl}}/edit/history
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}

### 46. Undo last edit (LIFO — also undoes bulk operations atomically)
POST {{baseUrl}}/edit/undo
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
Origin: http://localhost:3000

### 47. Export edited GTFS as ZIP
GET {{baseUrl}}/edit/export
X-Session-ID: {{sessionId}}
